                                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[How I Created the Ultimate Rescue Drive for My PCs]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/how-i-created-the-ultimate-rescue-drive-for-my-pcs/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Ali Haider]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/hand-inserting-a-usb-flash-drive-labeled-rescue-sos-into-a-laptop.png" length="3261" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Linux]]></category><category><![CDATA[Ubuntu]]></category><category><![CDATA[storage]]></category><category><![CDATA[PC Optimization]]></category><category><![CDATA[Backup & Recovery]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            A pocket-sized lifeline for your computer.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Imagine this: you come home, turn on your PC or laptop, and it won’t boot. Now what? You had important work to do. Panic sets in, and you don’t know what to do next.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Thu, 11 Sep 2025 13:30:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/how-i-created-the-ultimate-rescue-drive-for-my-pcs/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[2025 VW ID.4 vs. Ioniq 5 vs. Kia EV6: Which Electric SUV Is the Best Deal?]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/2025-electric-suv-best-deal/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Adam Gray]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/id4-ev6-ioniq5-feature.jpg" length="250" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Automotive]]></category><category><![CDATA[Electric Vehicles]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            These three electric SUVs compete closely, but one offers the best deal for 2025 buyers.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>The <a href="https://www.howtogeek.com/2-year-old-tesla-worth-buying-used/" target="_blank">Tesla Model Y</a> may still be the best-selling electric crossover in 2025, but cracks are starting to show. Sales have slipped hard over the past few months, and plenty of shoppers are eyeing other options.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Thu, 11 Sep 2025 13:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/2025-electric-suv-best-deal/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[The Best Non-MCU Marvel Movies You Can Stream Right Now]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/best-non-mcu-marvel-movies-you-can-stream-right-now/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Chris Snellgrove]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wolverine-spider-man-and-blade-with-the-marvel-logo-above-and-cinematic-universe-crossed-out.png" length="2639" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Streaming]]></category><category><![CDATA[Streaming]]></category><category><![CDATA[Disney+]]></category><category><![CDATA[ Movies]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            The top non-MCU Marvel films that pack a punch, from iconic Spider-Man to gritty Blade. Stream these action-packed classics now!
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>While the brand has lost some of its luster in recent years, the average person still associates Marvel movies with the MCU, the cinematic universe that brought us everything from <em>Iron Man</em> to <em>The Thunderbolts</em>. But the MCU wasn’t born until 2008, and there were plenty of Marvel films created before that. And even after that, there have been more films made outside of the MCU umbrella than you can shake an Infinity Gauntlet at.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Thu, 11 Sep 2025 12:30:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/best-non-mcu-marvel-movies-you-can-stream-right-now/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[I Went Back and Booted the First Linux Distro I Ever Tried]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/i-went-back-and-booted-the-first-linux-distro-i-ever-tried/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[David Delony]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/08/3d-illustration-of-tux-the-linux-penguin-mascot-depicted-as-an-elderly-figure-with-a-white-beard-glasses-and-a-cane-standing-in-front-of-a-display-showcasing-some-linux-distros.png" length="1590" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Linux]]></category><category><![CDATA[Linux & macOS Terminal]]></category><category><![CDATA[Tech Throwback]]></category><category><![CDATA[Open Source]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            You never forget your first distro.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Nearly every Linux user seems to remember their first encounter with the OS. I decided to try booting up the first distro I ever tried, Knoppix, to see how well it held up since I first tried it over 20 years ago.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Thu, 11 Sep 2025 12:00:17 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/i-went-back-and-booted-the-first-linux-distro-i-ever-tried/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[The iPhone Plus Is Dead, Here's What You Should Buy Instead]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/the-iphone-plus-is-dead-heres-what-you-should-buy-instead/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Tim Brookes]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/iphone-16-plus-and-16-with-the-16-plus-fading.jpg" length="494" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Iphone]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple iPhone 17]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple iPhone Air]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple iPhone 17 Pro Max]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            The Plus isn't really gone, it's just changed a bit.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Lost among the fanfare about the iPhone Air and the iPhone 17 Pro’s chunky camera block is news of a fallen comrade: the Plus-sized base model iPhone. This is bad news for anyone who preferred a larger screen, but there are still some options available.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Thu, 11 Sep 2025 11:00:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/the-iphone-plus-is-dead-heres-what-you-should-buy-instead/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Google Pixel 10 Review: So Good I'm Skipping the Pro Model This Year]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/google-pixel-10-review/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Joe Fedewa]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/09/google-pixel-10-8.jpg" length="2613" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Android]]></category><category><![CDATA[Google Pixel 10]]></category><category><![CDATA[Google Pixel]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            No longer just an afterthought.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>As a long-time Pixel owner, last year’s release took me by surprise. I didn’t think the series needed a refresh, but I was quickly won over. This year, the <a href="https://store.google.com/product/pixel_10?hl=en-US" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" target="_blank">Google Pixel 10</a> is more of the same, and some critical upgrades make me feel like I don’t need the Pro version anymore.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Thu, 11 Sep 2025 10:00:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/google-pixel-10-review/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[The AirPods Pro 3 Are Missing Something In The Box]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/the-airpods-pro-3-are-missing-something-in-the-box/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Arol Wright]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/airpods-pro-3-hero.jpg" length="95" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Iphone]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple AirPods Pro 3]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Apple being Apple.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>The AirPods Pro 3 are here, and they're a huge jump from the AirPods Pro 2 in almost every way. But I hope you have a cable lying around, because Apple is not shipping one with its newest earbuds.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Wed, 10 Sep 2025 22:43:22 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/the-airpods-pro-3-are-missing-something-in-the-box/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[I've Bought Every Flagship iPhone, But This Year I'm Skipping the 17 Pro]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/ive-bought-every-flagship-iphone-but-this-year-im-skipping-the-17-pro/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Bryan M. Wolfe]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/iphone-17-pro-1.jpeg" length="405" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Iphone]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple iPhone 17 Pro]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple iPhone 17 Pro Max]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Is the newest iPhone Pro worth the investment? I'm not convinced.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Apple's first Pro smartphone arrived in 2019 as the iPhone 11 Pro, and ever since then I’ve routinely purchased the latest Pro Max model. This year I'm skipping the recently introduced iPhone 17 Pro, and this significant change is not a decision I have taken lightly.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Wed, 10 Sep 2025 22:00:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/ive-bought-every-flagship-iphone-but-this-year-im-skipping-the-17-pro/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[How to Enable the God Folder on Windows 11]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/god-mode-in-windows-11-changed-how-i-use-my-pc-forever/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Aman Kumar]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/a-notebook-with-the-windows-11-file-explorer-open-and-the-file-explorer-icon-in-the-front.jpg" length="986" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[Windows 11]]></category><category><![CDATA[Microsoft]]></category><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            A one-stop destination for all your Windows settings.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>If you’ve been using Windows for quite some time now, then you must have heard about God Mode. Don’t worry if you haven’t heard about it before, as I will share everything about Windows God Mode and how it completely changed the way I use my Windows PC.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Wed, 10 Sep 2025 21:15:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/god-mode-in-windows-11-changed-how-i-use-my-pc-forever/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[These Simple Tweaks Made Edge My Favorite Browser ]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/these-tweaks-made-edge-my-favorite-browser/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Faisal Rasool]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/microsoft-edge-browser-interface-featuring-a-large-edge-logo-at-the-center-with-a-prominent-search-bar-below-and-some-stylized-gears-in-the-background-1.png" length="592" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Microsoft]]></category><category><![CDATA[web browsers]]></category><category><![CDATA[chromium-edge]]></category><category><![CDATA[internet]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Let's take the Microsoft out of the Edge browser.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Microsoft Edge feels like a billboard more than a browser, which is why I've never used it as my default. Recently, though, I installed Windows on a laptop that was too old to run even a regular browser, so I ended up spending some time with Edge. Turns out, it can be a solid browser with a few tweaks.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Wed, 10 Sep 2025 20:16:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/these-tweaks-made-edge-my-favorite-browser/</guid></item></channel>
